    • Constructor Detail

      • CypRel

        public CypRel(int posInClause,
              java.lang.String id,
              java.lang.String type,
              com.google.gson.JsonObject props,
              java.lang.String direction)
        Constructor for recording information about a Cypher relationship/edge. Example match clause: MATCH (a)<-[r1 : REL_TYPE_A]-(b)-[r2 {state:8}]-(c)-[r3]->(d) ...
        Parameters:
        posInClause - The position in the match clause that the relationship fits into to. In the example, the edge with id 'r1' is in position 1, and the edge with id 'r3' is in position 3.
        id - The id of the edge (if it has one): in the example, these are identified by r1, r2, and r3.
        type - The type of the edge being stored: in the example, the first relationship ('r1') has type 'REL_TYPE_A'.
        props - If the edge holds and properties, then it is stored in this field. The properties does not include the type of edge, only the JSON object.
        direction - The direction of the edge: in the example above, all three directions are shown: the edge with id 'r1' = 'left' the edge with id 'r2' = 'none' the edge with id 'r3' = 'right'
